6Title: This week in Nushell #271
Path: Nushell
Content:
Kissaki 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14230] improved comment wording in run_external.rs
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14229] fixed comment typos in run_external.rs
vyadh 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14225] added tests for new Alpine and Debian image builds
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14193] added a Debian Dockerfile
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14210] prevented subcommand execution when surrounded with backtick quotes
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14209] added a RELEASE_QUERY_API build arg for Dockerfiles
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14191] updated the dockerfile for Alpine
hacker-DOM 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14201] allowed using function keys F21-F35 for keybindings
aionescu 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14198] dropped 
``once_cell``
 dependency
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14197] improved 
``CellPath``
 display output
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14180] fixed quoting in 
``to nuon``
 and refactored quoting functions
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14042] added 
``?``
 for optional entries when displaying 
``CellPath``
s
NotTheDr01ds did a bunch of work related to escape sequences: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14196] added previews of attributes to 
``ansi -l``
 (e.g., bold, dimmed, blink, etc.)
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14184] fixed the name for 
``ansi clear_entire_screen_plus_buffer``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14181] sent both 2J and 3J on clear
ofek 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14192] ensured default config files end with a new line
sgvictorino 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14190] added support for table literal syntax in 
``join``
 right-table argument
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14187] allowed OEM code pages to be used to decode text
friaes 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14175] updated 
``stor insert``
 to accept lists
Bahex 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14173] provided a common implementation for query string conversions in 
``url join``
 and 
``url build-query``
qfel 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14083] added the history import command (again)
blindFS 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14002] fixed LSP non-ASCII character offset issues
íŔ@11b5ebc31badb553ecc8894c8b31a8f515f2c73d9004253bac7f6bc4f6dcf4bbŕTitle: This week in Nushell #271
Path: Documentation
Content:
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1612] changed "local environment" example (yet again!)
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1610] fixed Creating Modules code example (a bit further)
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1600] updated "Working with Tables" - added info on "index renaming" and the table command
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1598] fixed type signatures on custom commands
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1597] rewrote Module chapter
Kissaki 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1609] fixed 'Creating Modules' code examples
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1607] improved Nerd Fonts docs
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1606] fixed typo in code example
vyadh 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1601] added candidate naming convention to the style guide
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1594] added example showing discovery and running of test commands
amkhlv 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1599] wrapped script in "def main 
[
]
 {...}"
kubouch 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1596] removed unsupported syntax from type signatures
victorhck 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/1589] updated spanish Readme translation
